HEADWORD: Stem-winder
<hw>Stem"-wind`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
stem-winding watch.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(Fig.)</mark> <def>Anything
of superior quality, as was attributed to the stem-winding watch; --
esp. used to describe a stirring speech, as in the phrase ⟦ldquo⟧a
<ex>stem-winder</ex> of a speech⟦rdquo⟧ or ⟦ldquo⟧delivered a
<ex>stem-winder</ex>⟦rdquo⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stem-winding</ent>⟦br⟧
